thread.title: Brush fire burns structures and cars south of Bennett
thread.title_full: Brush fire burns structures and cars south of Bennett - The Denver Post

author: Tom McGhee
title: Brush fire burns structures and cars south of Bennett
text:
A brush fire south of Bennett burned multiple structures and cars on Sunday but caused no injuries, officials said. Fire authorities declared the blaze had been contained.
There were no injuries in the fire near Bennett, at 7147 S. Kincaid St., east of Denver along Interstate 70, said MetCom spokesperson Angie Johnson.
She didn't know whether the structures involved were homes or other buildings.
The Arapahoe County Sheriff's Office tweeted that one building and nine cars were lost. It said the fire was fully contained.
Poudre Fire Authority and the Wellington Fire Department are also working a brush fire, the Larimer County Sheriff's Office said Sunday.
"Looks like fire crews have this one knocked down. Fire is still under the command of Wellington Fire," Larimer County Sheriff Justin Smith said via Twitter.
This is a developing story that will be updated when more information is available.
